<HL>
   Philips Industries Sets Meeting
</HL>
<DATE>
08/06/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C9
</SO>
<CO>
   PHL TOMKY
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
BUILDING MATERIALS (BLD)
</IN>
<LP>
   DAYTON, Ohio -- Philips Industries Inc. said shareholders
will meet Aug. 22 to consider its agreement to be acquired by
Tomkins PLC for $18.50 a share, or $550 million.
   The maker of building and industrial products said the
British company may buy up to 10%, or 2,860,000, of Philips's
shares outstanding before the acquisition.
